{"ts": "2026-06-08T13:38:28.260409+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 4c386b25d56ec24baa2939d718ff0c3708c8627b)", "id": "lc_5c682468-e79e-4935-8d68-99dd2349d164"}, {"type": "text", "text": "name: release-main\n\non:\n  push:\n    branches: [main]\n\njobs:\n  ci:\n    runs-on: ${{ matrix.os }}\n\n    strategy:\n      matrix:\n        os: [ubuntu-latest]\n\n    steps:\n      - name: Checkout 🛎\n        uses: actions/checkout@v4\n        with:\n          fetch-depth: 0\n\n      - name: Setup node env 🏗\n        uses: actions/setup-node@v4\n        with:\n          node-version-file: '.nvmrc'\n          check-latest: true\n\n      - name: Setup pnpm 📦\n        uses: pnpm/action-setup@v4\n        with:\n          package_json_file: package.json\n\n      - name: Install dependencies 📦\n        run: pnpm install\n\n      - name: Run linter 👀\n        run: pnpm run lint-fix\n\n      - name: Run tests 🧪\n        run: pnpm run test:unit\n\n      - name: Build\n        run: pnpm run build\n  release:\n    runs-on: ${{ matrix.os }}\n    needs: ci\n\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write\n      contents: write    \n\n    strategy:\n      matrix:\n        os: [ubuntu-latest]\n\n    steps:\n      - name: Checkout 🛎\n        uses: actions/checkout@v4\n        with:\n          fetch-depth: 0\n\n      - name: Setup node env 🏗\n        uses: actions/setup-node@v4\n        with:\n          node-version-file: '.nvmrc'\n          check-latest: true\n\n      - name: Setup pnpm 📦\n        uses: pnpm/action-setup@v4\n        with:\n          package_json_file: package.json\n\n      - name: Install dependencies 📦\n        run: pnpm install\n\n      - name: Install semantic-release extra plugins 📦\n        run: pnpm install --save-dev semantic-release @semantic-release/changelog @semantic-release/git\n\n      - name: Release\n        env:\n          GITHUB_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\n        run: npx semantic-release\n", "id": "lc_d60c644e-380c-4c62-b7f1-c488e3924d12"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "af08c493-c9d3-4878-9740-fa801377799d", "tool_call_id": "call_00_G0wII45hUWxsA7DmUuIl2328", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-08T13:38:36.492448+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on the repository contents, **contributors are expected to use pnpm, and npm is not acceptable**. Here is the evidence:\n\n---\n\n### 1. `package.json` – explicit package manager declaration and enforcement\n\n- **`\"packageManager\": \"pnpm@10.20.0\"`** – [package.json](https://github.com/rpnr-bench/T01_R01/blob/main/package.json) formally declares pnpm as the package manager.\n- **`\"preinstall\": \"npx only-allow pnpm\"`** – the `preinstall` script uses the [`only-allow`](https://www.npmjs.com/package/only-allow) package, which **blocks installation if the package manager is not pnpm**. If someone tries `npm install`, the script will fail with a clear error message telling them to use pnpm instead.\n\n```json\n\"scripts\": {\n  \"preinstall\": \"npx only-allow pnpm\",\n  ...\n}\n```\n\n### 2. Lock file – only pnpm lock file present\n\nThe repository contains **`pnpm-lock.yaml`** but no `package-lock.json` (npm) or `yarn.lock` (yarn). This signals that the project is managed exclusively with pnpm.\n\n### 3. CI workflow – pnpm is the only tool used\n\nThe [release workflow](https://github.com/rpnr-bench/T01_R01/blob/main/.github/workflows/release.yml) installs and uses pnpm in every step:\n\n```yaml\n- name: Setup pnpm 📦\n  uses: pnpm/action-setup@v4\n  with:\n    package_json_file: package.json\n\n- name: Install dependencies 📦\n  run: pnpm install\n\n- name: Run linter 👀\n  run: pnpm run lint-fix\n\n- name: Run tests 🧪\n  run: pnpm run test:unit\n\n- name: Build\n  run: pnpm run build\n```\n\n### 4. README – instructions use pnpm\n\nThe [README](https://github.com/rpnr-bench/T01_R01/blob/main/README.md) shows all setup steps with `pnpm`:\n\n```\npnpm install\npnpm run dev\npnpm run build\npnpm run test:unit\npnpm run lint\n```\n\n---\n\n**Conclusion:** Contributors **must** use pnpm. The repository is configured to reject npm usage at install time via the `only-allow` preinstall hook, and every aspect of the project (lock file, CI, documentation) is built around pnpm.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 852, "prompt_tokens": 5630, "total_tokens": 6482, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 300, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 4992}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 4992, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 638}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-flash", "system_fingerprint": "fp_8b330d02d0_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "5656535e-c95f-4f7b-bc1d-e053d6b36ab1", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea774-c525-7b90-92fc-8e114aabf19b-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 5630, "output_tokens": 852, "total_tokens": 6482, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 4992}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 300}}}}]}}}
